Rating: 3
I've found these to be a real crowd pleaser. Some tips that may help: Paint the outside of the seal with some egg wash before wrapping. Use your sharpest serrated knife to cut, but first use a flat edge of the knife to press on the seal- more effective than fingers. Use the flat side of the knife to pack the open end before each cut. If you've never used parchment paper, try it now! It's like waxed paper for the oven: your pinwheels will slide right off.

Rating: 4
