Rating: 0
To Ana on 4/2/03 A suggestion for the saltiness you mentioned: 1. could be the prosciutto sat in pkg too long, but is still very good, but salty. You can by feeling the meat and you will feel the salt crystals. Simply rinse under water faucet and pat dry. Also, the Gruyere has 160 mg of sodium per 1 oz (1" cube). Emmentaler has 50 mg sodium for same size. You might want to try using half and half.

