Rating: 4
I have been making these pinwheels for ~7yrs. The original version of this recipe first appeared in Gourmet, on the back page in the mid '90s. Anyway this has become a BIG favorite in our house and among our friends. The original recipe called for fresh sage instead of basil. Sage is more pungent than basil and in combination with the other ingrediants, makes a nice combination. Also, you can tell the difference in quality between American and authentic Prosciutto Di Parma. If you can find it, buy the imported. It is sweeter and more assertive.

Rating: 4
Fabulous hors d'oeuvre! I make this using the sage not the basil. You can also bake off a whole batch of these and freeze them in small freezer bags, say a dozen in each, and pull them out when you need them. Just heat in a toaster oven and serve. They keep in the freezer for about three months.

