I made a "Skyye" version of this recipe and it was fabulous. I am rather clumsy with delicate dishes, so I spread out the puff pastry, but layered about 7 of them on top of each other to make a thick crust. I placed the basil out first on the crust, put a light layer of hunts tomato sauce over the basil, added the prosciutto, and then added the gruyere/mozzarella mix I made and baked with out rolling, as I said before, I am not graceful with delicate dishes. This modified version was great. My companion demands I make pinwheels once a week for dinner (too filling for us as an appetizer). Sometimes I add pineapple for a little flair. We love this innovative culinary delight! Cheers

